snippet.textDisplay: I'm super confused, how did they go from expecting 160kw to getting 215kw?, nearly 100kw over original spec?  What happened?  Also I think it's more that the S13 is the parts bin car - the Pulsar, specifically the 4 door Pulsar was a high volume vehicle, the Sylvia a low volume - so the parts would likely have been designed for the Pulsar and appropriated by the Sylvia rather than the other way around.  I guess in Australia you probably don't see a lot of these high volume Japanese 90's OEM vehicles as it'd be the low volume ones that got imported more.

snippet.textDisplay:
Ahh.. The Nissan Sunny GTiR (as it's called in Europe).
What a mad little car. High performance and 4WD packed into a compact shell, like a Japanese answer to the Golf Rallye, Golf G60 Syncro, and other European hot hatchbacks from the same era.
I believe Mazda also made a high performance version of the 323 hatchback called the GTR. These small cars are the absolute definition of "fun on four wheels"

Good to see you restored this one, as these cars are totally worth it :)
